data.title: Teenage Kicks
data.text:
Song Information

Artist: The Undertones

Composition/Lyrics: John O'Neill

Album: The Undertones (1979)

BPM: 135

Length: 1:34

First Music Game Appearance: Dancing Stage Fever (PlayStation 2)

Other Music Game Appearances: None.

Lyrics

Are teenage dreams so hard to beat? Every time she walks down the street. Another girl in the neighbourhood. I wish she was mine, she looks so good. I wanna hold her, wanna hold her tight. Get teenage kicks right through the night. Are teenage dreams so hard to beat? Every time she walks down the street. Another girl in the neighbourhood. I wish she was mine, she looks so good. I wanna hold her, wanna hold her tight. Get teenage kicks right through the night. I wanna hold her, wanna hold her tight. Get teenage kicks right through the night.

Song Connections / Remixes

Teenage Kicks has been covered by many artists, including Ash, Franz Ferdinand, Supergrass and KT Tunstall.

Trivia

Teenage Kicks features its music video, eliminating any on-screen dancers.

Teenage Kicks is not a constant 135 BPM. The tempo fluctuates throughout the song, ranging from 131.87 to 137.4 BPM.

Song Production Information

None.

Difficulty & Notecounts

DanceDanceRevolution difficulty rated from 1 to 10 from DDRMAX2 to SuperNOVA2.
